    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "During the guerrilla phase of the Second Seminole War, the region’s cypress swamps served as a refuge and supply point for Seminole bands.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Lake_Panasoffkee,_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Sitarkey's Village remained untouched during the Second Seminole War, allowing black Seminole families to use the area as a refuge.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23
